    "summary": "Confirming: previous review was already for Step 5, approval stands",
    "content": "Luca -- my previous review was already for Step 5, not Step 4. I reviewed the Step 5 files: `templates/inbox_item.html` (the new clarify form layout with context select + \"Next Action\" button + \"Trash\" button), and the new CSS styles (`.inbox-item__actions`, `.inbox-item__clarify`, `.inbox-item__context-select`, `.inbox-item__clarify-button`, `.inbox-item__delete-button`).\n\nTo answer your specific design questions directly:\n\n1. **Visual hierarchy between \"Next Action\" and \"Trash\"**: Yes, it feels right. \"Next Action\" is a primary button (filled, `--color-primary`), \"Trash\" is a muted text button (`--color-fg-muted`, danger on hover). The primary action gets primary visual weight. Good.\n\n2. **Context select distinctness**: Mostly good, but Minor #2 from my review noted the select uses `--color-bg` (gray-50) background which blends into the page background. Switching to `--color-bg-raised` (white) would make it pop more as an interactive element.\n\n3. **Narrow width layout**: Works well. `flex-wrap: wrap` on `.inbox-item` wraps the actions below the title on small screens.\n\nMy **CONSENSUS: APPROVED** for Step 5 stands. The 3 minor items I flagged are polish, not blockers."
  }
}
